# v0.5.21

## Add Lua integration for executing Glazed commands from Lua scripts

This release introduces Lua integration for Glazed, allowing users to
execute Glazed commands directly from Lua scripts. Key features include:

- Execute Glazed commands (GlazeCommand, BareCommand, WriterCommand) in Lua
- Convert between Lua and Glazed data structures
- Parse Lua tables into Glazed parameter layers
- Comprehensive documentation and tutorials for Lua integration

To get started, refer to the new Lua integration tutorial and
documentation using `glaze help lua` and `glaze help lua-tutorial`.

This feature opens up new possibilities for automating and
customizing Glazed command execution within Lua scripts.

